cs.NI, cs.CR, cs.AR, cs.IT, cs.DC 

This paper deals with optimizing end-to-end performance over diverse Internet paths, which is a common problem in networking. The paper proposes a new architecture called Tng, which is focused on transport services. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also deals with security issues related to in-path optimizers, which suggests that it could belong to cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also mentions communication over lossy wireless links, which could suggest that it belongs to cs.AR (Hardware Architecture). The paper also mentions reducing buffering-induced latency on residential links, which could suggest that it belongs to cs.IT (Information Theory). Finally, the paper proposes a new architecture, which could suggest that it belongs to cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing).
